  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Trade Accounting Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary:</strong></p><p>The Trade Accounting Executive is responsible for handling trade transactions and management reporting for our oleochemical business. This role involves preparing daily trade P&L reports, ensuring compliance with accounting standards, and supporting smooth collaboration between trading, operations, and finance teams. The ideal candidate should possess strong analytical skills, a solid understanding of IFRS, and experience in trade accounting within the oleochemical industry.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Record and reconcile all trade-related transactions, including recognition of sales, purchases, freight and other related expenses</li></ul><ul><li>Prepare daily trade P&L and mark-to-market reports</li></ul><ul><li>Ensure  timely and accurate recording of invoices, payments and trade-related accruals or adjustments for month-end closing</li></ul><ul><li>Maintain supporting documentation for intercompany transactions to ensure compliance with transfer pricing requirements </li></ul><ul><li>Collaborate with traders, operations and finance teams to support smooth business operations</li></ul><ul><li>Maintain proper documentation to support the company’s Global Trader Programme (GTP) status</li></ul><ul><li>Ensure adherence to internal controls, company policies, and International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS)</li></ul><ul><li>Maintain audit readiness and attend to queries and requirements from internal and external auditors</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field</li></ul><ul><li>Experience in trade accounting for commodities, preferably within the oleochemical  industry</li></ul><ul><li>Good understanding of accounting principles and Incoterms</li></ul><ul><li>Strong communication, problem-solving, and analytical skills</li></ul><ul><li>Ability to work independently and meet deadlines</li></ul><ul><li>Proficiency  in Microsoft Office (especially Excel)</li></ul><p></p>",
